 This install applies to "Disposable Hero" © 1993-94 Euphoria/Gremlin Graphics.

 This install requires WHDLoad and RawDIC to be in the path. Both can be found
 in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 1.0 MB ChipMem and 0.5 MB OtherMem (disk version)
                                0.5 MB ChipMem and 1.0 MB OtherMem (fast disk version)
                                2.0 MB ChipMem and 0.5 MB OtherMem (CD32 version)

 It can be quit by pressing Prtscr (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page.

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
   http://www.whdload.de/
 or   aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and  aminet:game/patch/

 version 1.5 (20.05.06) done by C-Fou!
 - ExitKey fixed on 68000
 - Access fault fixed on 68000 (odd adress)
 - Outro gfx bug fixed (caused by slave error in loader)
 - Another self-modifying codes rewritten (Intro & Outro)
 - Many blitter delays inserted in outro
 - 2 Slaves for disk version (one using fast memory but 'nocache' can be needed)
 - DOS intro crash fixed (ckecksum code protection resurrection ;))
 - WaitButton routine inserted between each levels (to see inter-level animations)
 - Stack relocated fixed
 - New install script
 - Source codes included
 - Many colored icons added
 - Tested on 68060

 version 1.4 (27.02.02) done by C-Fou!
 - another self-modifying codes rewritten (outro crashed)

 version 1.3 (08.02.02) done by C-Fou!
 - keyboard access fault in high-score debugged (with Cache on 060 for disk version)

 version 1.2 (22.10.01) done by C-Fou!
 - Crash when you skippped quickly DOS intro fixed (disk version)

 version 1.1 (05.10.01) done by C-Fou!
 - CD32 version supported (using OSEMU)
 - Load/Save high scores redirected on HD (file 'DisposableHero.save')
 - RAWDIC imager used
 - Keyboard routine included in CD32 version
 - CFou keyboard Trainer added for both versions
      F1    : 1 live added
      F2    : To activate original CHEAT MENU (option/configuration)
   Del/Help : To skip level
 - Sound bug skipping quickly  DOS intro fixed (disk version)
 - You can quit High Scores screen pressing 'Return' in CD32 version
   (To validate your name if you have'nt CD32 PAD)
 - fixed with SNOOP Tooltype 

 version 1.0
 - initial JST release
 - Only disks version supported

